03/05/2005
RAMALLAH, Palestinian Authority -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan reiterated on Monday (2 May) that his country is ready to act as a mediator in talks between Israel and the Palestinians if the two sides request it. Erdogan met with Palestinian National Authority President Mahmoud Abbas and Prime Minister Ahmed Qurei to discuss the Mideast peace process. Earlier, he met with Israeli leaders in Jerusalem. Both sides seem receptive to mediation by Turkey.
In other news Monday, inmates rioted at Istanbul's Umraniye prison, setting blankets and mattresses on fire. Police and firefighters put out the blaze before anyone was seriously injured. The cause of the riot was not immediately clear. (Anadolu Agency, Palestinian Satellite Channel TV, BBC, Reuters - 02/05/05)
